(enablePrefetching, numRCQEntries).explanation: Enabling prefetching increases memory traffic and requires more request completion queue entries to handle the additional prefetch requests and their completions;

(enablePrefetching, flush).explanation: Prefetching can increase pipeline flushes when mispredicted prefetches pollute caches or when prefetch-induced cache conflicts cause incorrect speculative execution paths;

(enablePrefetching, nICacheTLBWays).explanation: The number of instruction cache TLB ways is a fixed hardware configuration parameter that is independent of whether prefetching is enabled or disabled;
